headline: Warren Buffett Favorite Domino's Sees This as a Big Growth Driver, but Is the Stock a Buy?
summary: The chain's partnership with DoorDash is expected to drive growth later this year and beyond.  While Warren Buffett's Berkshire Hathaway was unloading hundreds of millions of dollars worth of equities last year, one of the few stocks it was buying was Domino's Pizza (NASDAQ: DPZ).  The largest pizza restaurant operator in the world, Domino's has a strong franchise and the type of global brand equity that Buffett likes to see in a consumer goods stock.
